<BR>
The $40/month on Legends is not to fix the current bugs in the game.  It is to provide dynamic content, more GM's, unique items, etc.  Do you honestly think they are goint to fix something like the Mail Quest (for example) on the Legends server but not implement it on the rest of the servers?  Show me a statement that indicates the BUGS will be fixed only on the Legends server.<BR>
<BR>
Now lets think about what you said.  You seem to think that for $12/month, Verant could provide what they are giving on the Legends server to everyone.  Wrong.  Sure, for $12/month they could hire some extra programers, but they couldn't provide all the other perks they are offering on Legends; GM's, Dynamic content, etc.<BR>
<BR>
You also seem to somehow know that Legends server will take away from the regular servers.  What basis do you have to claim this other than speculation?  Lets assume that some time in the last year or so Verant decided to invest money in Luclin and the Legends server.  What would make one take priority over another?  If a car company releases a car with a paint defect, and issues a recall, do they need to stop making/selling other model cars while the issue the recall.<BR>
<BR>
All I'm saying is wait and see how it pans out before you start screaming out of your ass, Torlaor.  I'm not going to shell out the $40 to play on this server.  But i'm going to wait and see if it affects me before I start screaming about how evil verant is and how i absolutely hate this game I play so much.<BR>
<BR>
You know, when Luclin came out, I was one of the few who was still running on Win95.  My 3 month subscription had just started another billing cycle and when I even mentioned the idea of wanting a refund for the 2 months left on my subscription, all you guys started shouting about how I should just deal with it.  So now I will say the same thing to you Tolaor.  If you Don't like it.... Don't Play!<BR>
<BR>
But why don't you wait and see if all the horrible things you have imagined actually happen before you decide.
