				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I learned a few things from all of these posts, I also have a few ideas of my own about why they created the Legends Server(s). Humor me:<BR>
<BR>
1) 9 out of 10 posters (being leberal) do not like the idea of the new &quot;better&quot; server. If this were to be a typical cross section of all EQ players, 90% of EQ doesn't like it.<BR>
<BR>
2) Sony's accounting department flunked basic Economics. $10x400,000 (subscribers)=$4mil. per monthx12 =$48 million. Now, their new Legends server allows, let's say, 8000 people on it for $40 a month: $40x8000x12=$3.84 million per year (pocket change compared to base subscription price.)<BR>
<BR>
3) (Mike is missing this one, I think) Legends is to be more bug-free than any other server. Meaning they FIXED a lot of OUR bugs we were PAYING them to fix, and they PROMISED to fix them. Well, they kept their promise and fixed the bugs, just not on regular servers. <BR>
<BR>
4) It was said that 80%(?) of on-line gamers WOULD pay an extra dollar a month to play their game. OK, if Sony charged everyone $11 instead of $10 they would generate $4.8 million a year. Hmmm, that's only $40,000 less than the legends server will be generating, and they won't have for service on the new computers needed for Legends. Hell, the servers needed for Legends alone will cost more than $40,000. (I'm in the industry, I know what I'm talking about)<BR>
<BR>
Now take all that into considertion, if we all paid $12 a month instead of $10 a month Sony would have no excuses for the sh!tty SC and the attitudes of the sh!tty GMs who won't help you when you've been killed multiple times because of a bug they won't fix. An extra $2 bucks a month from current subscribers will geberate almost 10million a year for them, more than enough to get PROPER CS and programmers to help us out. For Chrit's sake, the Gnoll Slayer quest is still frickin broke from the original starter game.<BR>
<BR>
Now, here are my thoughts on why they are doing this despite the economical retardedness. They start with Legends, then they turn around and say &quot;We've hired more programmers with the profits from Legends.&quot; when in fact it is the exact same programmers they hired FOR legends. They copy the 95% bug-free code from Legends onto ALL the other servers and tell us&quot;You have to pay the same price as the Legends server now, because you are as bug-free as they are and have access to the same stuff we promised you. We fixed it like you asked but it took an entire server to do it, so now you pay or leave.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
That's my opinion, I may be wrong.<BR>
