	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				If you call your Cable Co. no matter what level of service you have you get the same CS people and the same support. It doesnt matter if you have basic cable or the full digital every channel ever created package.<BR>
   The idea of a new level of EQ service on a different server for $40 a month doesnt bother me(i wont be signing up)but it does bother me that regular EQ subscribers will lose things.<BR>
   First off, when they staff this new server do you think they will pull people off the street to hire for these positions? NO, they will use their experienced CS ppl for this. Oh, there will be 2 completely seperate teams but experienced employees will be hired/promoted to the premium EQ service and the newbs will be put in the regular EQ cs. If you were going to start a premium service advertised with superior CS wouldnt you staff it with experienced &quot;capable&quot; employees?<BR>
    Do you think they will do the same with programmers? If this new service will have all the new equipment,items and scenarios first<BR>
would you staff it with a team of newly hired programmers and CS people new to EQ? NO, again, you would move your best/most experienced people to the premium/uber team.<BR>
    Imagine how many more pissed off people VI will have to deal with if the Legends service bombs because they cant provide the service they promised. Add that to the people already pissed off because of the whole Legends idea. How many people will be left playing EQ.<BR>
    Ive seen alot of good points in the posts I have read and agree with many of them. Personally, I will not pay extra money for a service that in my opinion will not be worth the cost. <BR>
    But, I must say that I'm upset about the CS/support that I will be losing.<BR>
    Next time you're looking for that one GM on your server that knew what he was doing and  was actually able to help you.....dont be suprised if you dont find him because he got promoted to Legends and you dont pay $40 a month.<BR>
    I guess it doesnt really matter. Some people will pay for Legends and others won't. Hopefully it wont affect me.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
